ZCZC GE03
EXTENDED OUTLOOK
SUNDAY TO WEDNESDAY
ISSUED BY THE MET OFFICE ON BEHALF OF THE MARITIME AND COASTGUARD AGENCY
AT 202300 UTC
ANTICYCLONIC CONDITIONS DOMINATE ACROSS NERN CULLERCOATS ON SUNDAY EVENING
AS AN AREA OF HIGH PRESSURE 1027 ACROSS THE NORWEGIAN BASIN AMPLIFIES A RIDGE
SWARDS ACROSS THE N SEA. MEANWHILE A SHALLOW LOW ACROSS GERMANY AND POLAND
EXTENDS A TROUGH N INTO THE SERN N SEA AND WWARDS THROUGH THE ENGLISH CHANNEL.
A SECOND AREA OF HIGH PRESSURE 1027 LIES W OF BISCAY AT THE SAME TIME. THROUGH
MONDAY THE LOW DRIFTS AWAY SE ALLOWING THE TROUGH TO RELAX AS THE HIGH W
OF BISCAY DRIFTS NWARDS TO BECOME SLOW MOV ACROSS SCOTLAND WHILST INTSF.
THIS HIGH CONTINUES TO DOMINATE CONDITIONS ACROSS CULLERCOATS THROUGH TUESDAY
WHILE A NEW LOW DEVELOPS ACROSS THE NORWEGIAN SEA AND TRACKS SE INTO THE
NERN BALTIC ON WEDNESDAY. THIS EXTENDS A TROUGH WWARDS INTO THE N SEA INTERACTING
WITH THE HIGH TO BRING A RISK OF NEAR GALE TO GALE FORCE WINDS ACROSS THE
EERN N SEA
NNNN